review_blob: This is not a very complex beer at all, you need to keep it in your mouth for a long time to pick up the very subtle flavours.
Decent lager to buy large quantities of as its pretty cheap. Not a bad flavour or aroma but nothing too special about it.
Ive had this on draught a few times. This is the best Irish beer ever brewed, a beautiful big bold double IPA, hoppy goodness.
beer_name: Galway Bay Of Foam and Fury

review_blob: This is a pretty great refreshing, lightly coloured, easy to drink Irish pale ale, It has just enough hops to keep you hooked. Well worth a try if you can find it on tap because its not in bottles yet!
this is a big hopped, slighty bitter IPA, not one to rush, enjoy it slowly and let it warm you up.
